parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause coolant to leak onto the floor, potentially causing injury to occupants, and can also lead to reduced visibility due to steamed-up windows, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Coolant leaking from under the dashboard
coolant splattering on the driver and passenger side floor
coolant spraying into the engine compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of stress cracks in the rear windshield can cause it to shatter, potentially causing injury to occupants and reducing visibility while driving.
symptoms: stress cracks in the rear windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate lubrication of the differential can cause it to lock up, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential damage to the drivetrain.
Failure of the CV joints can cause loss of power to the wheels, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential damage to the drivetrain.
symptoms: Clicking or clunking noises from the front wheels
loss of power to the wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaks in the transmission's final drive can cause the transmission to lock up, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential damage to the transmission.
The failure of the coolant hoses can cause coolant leaks, overheating, and engine damage, which can lead to vehicle fires, engine failure, and accidents.
The failure of the fuel system can cause a sudden explosion or fire, resulting in serious injury or death, as well as significant damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: sudden explosion or fire near the fuel tank area

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks, especially if the vehicle stalls in traffic.
symptoms: vehicle stalls or fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to suddenly and unexpectedly accelerate, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
the vehicle accelerates without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle accelerates even when the brake pedal is pressed
the vehicle is difficult to control or stop.
